# Testing — Build & Quality Gates (No Unit Tests)

**Firma:** HorosCode · **Produkt:** HorosCloud

Pass 1 Mockup→Code requires **build and static quality checks** — not unit test suites.

## Mandatory Before "Done" Per Region

| Check | Command / Action | Must pass |
|-------|------------------|-----------|
| Build | `dotnet build` | Exit code 0 |
| Lint | `ReadLints` on changed files | Zero errors |
| Type check | Compiler / IDE diagnostics | Zero errors |
| Preview runs | Isolated `*Preview.axaml` | Renders without crash |
| Accessibility | Manual checklist (review) | Part of 98 score |

## Build Example

```bash
dotnet build HorosCloud.Desktop/HorosCloud.Desktop.csproj
```

Fix all compiler errors before screenshot review. **Never** suppress with `#pragma` or `@ts-ignore` equivalents.

## Accessibility Minimum (Pass 1)

```xml
<!-- Every interactive control -->
<Button AutomationProperties.Name="Save changes"
        Classes="primary"
        MinWidth="40" MinHeight="40" />

<!-- Focus visible via theme -->
<Style Selector="Button:focus-visible">
  <Setter Property="BorderBrush" Value="{DynamicResource BrushBorderFocus}" />
  <Setter Property="BorderThickness" Value="2" />
</Style>
```

| Check | Criterion |
|-------|-----------|
| Contrast | ≥ 4.5:1 normal text, ≥ 3:1 large text |
| Focus | Keyboard Tab shows visible focus ring |
| Names | `AutomationProperties.Name` on buttons, inputs, nav |
| Touch target | ≥ 40×40 px for interactive controls |

## Not Required in Pass 1

- Unit tests (`xUnit`, `NUnit`)
- Integration tests
- UI automation tests
- Performance benchmarks

## Never

- **Never** report success with failing `dotnet build`
- **Never** ignore linter errors on modified files
- **Never** skip accessibility because "it's just Pass 1"
- **Never** delete failing tests to pass CI (N/A for Pass 1 — but never in any pass)

